commitResults.messageBody:
Changes made in this commit:
1) Initialize the basic I/O features of the programme.

Changes made in this commit:
1) Created a list to add and monitor input items.

Changes made in this commit:
1) Implemented feature to mark Task as done.

Changes made in this commit:
1) Created the abstract Task class and various subclasses of Task.

Tasks are now distinct objects instead of just Strings. Each task
displays slightly different wordings on print.

Changes made in this commit:
1) Introduced abstract Task class and implemented various subclasses.

Task are now distinct objects instead of just a String name as in the
third level.

Changes made in this commit:
1) Provided support to compare actual output against expected output

Changes made in this commit:
1) Included checks for various error inputs

Included a InvalidCommandException and EmptyDescriptionException to
check for faulty inputs.

Changes made in this commit:
1) User can now delete a task from the existing list, provided the
   task index is valid in the first place.

commitResults.messageTitle: Minor refactoring to task adding processes.
commitResults.messageBody:
Changes made in this commit:
1) Separate the handling of actions and the adding of Tasks to
   taskList.

Changes made to this commit:
1) Allow taskList to be saved on disk while running program and
   loaded from disk on restart.

Changes made to this commit:
1) Restrict Deadline Task to take in only a specific date and time
   format as argument after the /by keyword.

Changes made in this commit:
1) Added TaskList, Storage, Parser and Ui classes to extract
   codes that are cluttered all over the main method in Duke.
2) Added Command and CommandCentre class to provide a more
   general way of adding new actions and their implementations
   to the chatbot.

Changes made in this commit:
1) Classified all classes into the relevant packages and updated
   access modifiers for methods affected.

Changes made in this commit:
1) Implemented Unit Testing with JUnit for specific cases in
   Parser and TaskList to handle different types of input.

Methods tested can be found in
src/test/java/package_name_of_method/NameOfClassBeingTestedTest.

The method names in the Test classes are in the following format
whatIsBeingTested_descriptionOfTestInputs_expectedOutcome().

If there are no test inputs. It is simply
whatIsBeingTested_expectedOutcome().

Changes made to this commit:

commitResults.messageTitle: Tweak the code to comply with Google Java Style Guide.
commitResults.messageBody:
Changes made in this commit:
1) Modified code style to abide by a common coding standard.

Changes made to this commit:
1) Added documentation to Ui class.

Changes made in this commit:
1) Implemented GUI using Javafx library
2) Updated Parser such that it checks for valid date format for Events

fxml files and images were added to a newly created resources folder
to ensure the functioning of the javafx UI. As output must be constantly
managed as String in the dialog boxes, major refactoring has been made
to the Ui class such that every method that used to print a message to
the system now appends the message to a StringBuilder object before
being extracted as a String.

To be aligned with the Duke requirement, Event tasks can only accept
a specific Date format for the additional info like Deadline tasks.

Other notes:
The tick and cross symbols, along with the emoticon symbol found in
most warning messages, have been replaced with their unicode form as
their previous forms cannot be printed on the javafx ui.

Changes made in this commit:
1) Resolve all checkstyle errors raised by the checker.

This includes the removal of indentation for 'case' for 'switch'
statements, the commenting of String objects that require unicode
characters (namely the tick, cross and emoticon) as well as clean-ups
to the documentation. No changes are made to the behaviour of the
program.

commitResults.messageTitle: Rectify Junit test input for Parser method
commitResults.messageBody:
With the recent updates in previous commits, Event detail can only
accept a specific date format as argument after the "/at" keyword.
The Junit test method input has has been corrected to attain a
successful result for a correct input format.

commitResults.messageTitle: Use "assert" at certain key points in Ui, Storage and TaskList classes
Improve code quality throughout the project
commitResults.messageBody:
Major code cleanups to all java files, especially in Parser and Ui
classes.

Parser used to be involved in I/O procedures but its job is
now strictly narrowed to validating user input and returning the data
to backend in the correct form. Parser is also now fully involved in
catching exceptions caused by invalid user input formats.

Ui no longer holds a singleton design as it is simply not necessary.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add "undo" commands to allow undo-ing of previous commands.
commitResults.messageBody:
The "undo" command executes the opposite of the most recently
successfully executed command. It can be called repeatedly until
there is no more earlier commands executed in the current javafx
session.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add "sort" command to allow sorting of list
commitResults.messageBody:
List can now be sorted by name, deadline, type of task or status, based
on user input. An additional argument "r" also renders sorting by
reversed order. For example, "sort deadline" sorts the task by deadline
in normal order while "sort name r" sorts the task by name in reversed
order
